    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-10T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">492.119/11–1050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Thailand</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d84fn1">Repeated to Saigon as 547.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-10T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 10, 1950—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>481. From Commerce: Current deterioration of French position in Indochina focuses
                    attention upon adequacy of United States export controls with respect to
                    Indochina and Thailand. Your vigilance as indicated your message<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d84fn2">Not identified.</note> regarding local controls, end use and
                    consignee information regarding some proposed shipments and extent of reexports
                    and smuggling strategic goods is appreciated. However, Commerce feels need for
                    restating its obligation and concern regarding <pb facs="0173" n="159"
                        xml:id="pg_159"/> final disposition United States strategic goods going to
                    these areas and urges continuation and intensification your attention to efforts
                    Commies obtaining strategic goods via transshipment and smuggling and reporting
                    development for formulation policy and procedure changes here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
